end_gcode.3.0.0:
print_end    ;end script from macro
G91 ; set to relative
G0 Z15; ; move 15mm down
G90 ; absolute positioning again
G0 X70 Y135
M84

pause_print_gcode.3.0.0:
; Start Pause Print
; This pause GCode is changed in PrusaSlicer via the Print Settings -> Output Options -> G-Code Substititons
; This is due to how PrusaSlicer inserts the M117 message for pause at the start of any custom GCode in this
; box.  As such, to soft-park the toolhead, handle retractions, and more, this is done in custom G-Code inj-
; -ected before this message.  Furthering this, due to a bug in how Marlin handles M117 messages on our di-
; -splay, we use M0 instead, hence the use of the second G-Code substitution regex.
; Thank you for understanding.


G90; Set absolute coordinate moves
M83; set extruder relative.
G61 F15000 XY ; move to last XY position.
M400; wait for move to finish.
G4 P100; small delay (100ms) to get around desync issues.

G1 E.6 F300; Purge small amount of Cocoa Core via extruder after pause.

G61 F15000 Z; move to last Z position (10mm offset, probably)
M400; wait for move to finish.
G4 P100; small delay (100ms) to get around desync issues.

G92 E0; Set extruder to "zero" so that it's not remembered.
G1 E.00001 900; very small move to reset feedrate bug.

start_gcode.3.0.0:
G90 ; use absolute coordinates
M83 ; use relative distances for extrusion

G28; home all axes
G92 E0 ; set extruder pos to zero

; loading mesh
BED_MESH_PROFILE LOAD=default

G1 Z1.5 F4500

G1 Z1.5 F4500

G1 X131.75 Y133 Z3.2
G1 X128.625 Y133 Z.5 E.15
G1 X8.25 Y133 E.25 F900

G1 X8.25 Y130 F900
